cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a MAC protocol to enhance the performance of WLANs, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of multi-user spatial multiplexing technique, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the need for higher uplink capacity due to the popularity of cloud uploading services and telepresence applications, which are related to multimedia. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a unified MAC protocol to balance both the downlink and uplink throughput, which involves system design and control. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed MAC protocol may have implications on security and cryptography in WLANs, such as preventing unauthorized access and ensuring data confidentiality.
